The paper presents a new architecture for neural networks that generalizes convolutional neural networks (ConvNets). The paper focuses on the architecture's ability to achieve state-of-the-art accuracy with smaller networks, which suggests a focus on machine learning (cs.LG) and computer vision (cs.CV). The paper also discusses the use of unsupervised learning for initializing networks, which suggests a focus on neural networks (cs.NE) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI). Finally, the paper discusses the use of a new operator for realizing classical operators like ReLU and max-pooling, which suggests a focus on natural language processing (cs.CL).
